SIMPLE: irruption
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Irruption
<hw>Ir*rup"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>irruptio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>irruption</ets>. See
<er>Irrupted</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A bursting in; a sudden, violent rushing into a
place; <as>as, <ex>irruptions</ex> of the sea</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Lest evil tidings, with too rude <qex>irruption</qex>⟦br⟧
Hitting thy aged ear, should pierce too deep.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A sudden and violent inroad, or entrance of
invaders; <as>as, the <ex>irruptions</ex> of the Goths into
Italy</as>.</def> <rj><au>Addison.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Invasion; incursion; inroad. See
<er>Invasion</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Irruptive</ent>⟦br⟧
